Scenario: Player passes turn during action phase
  Given it is Alice's turn during the action phase
  And Alice has taken 2 actions already
  When Alice clicks the "Pass" button
  Then Alice's turn ends immediately
  And the next player in turn order becomes active
  And Alice cannot take any more actions this round
  And the game log shows "Alice passed"

Scenario: All players pass advances to combat phase
  Given a 3-player game in the action phase
  And Alice, Bob, and Carol have all passed
  When the last player passes
  Then the game phase transitions to "Combat"
  And sectors with multiple players are identified for combat
  And the combat resolution UI appears
  And the action phase UI is hidden

Scenario: Round advances after all phases complete
  Given the game is in the cleanup phase
  And all cleanup tasks are complete
  When the cleanup phase finishes
  Then the round counter increments by 1
  And the game returns to the action phase
  And players' actions are reset
  And the first player in turn order becomes active

Scenario: Turn order rotates correctly
  Given a 4-player game with turn order: Alice, Bob, Carol, Dave
  And it is Alice's turn
  When Alice passes
  Then it becomes Bob's turn
  When Bob passes
  Then it becomes Carol's turn
  When Carol passes
  Then it becomes Dave's turn
  When Dave passes
  Then the action phase ends

Scenario: Player can see whose turn it is
  Given a 3-player game in the action phase
  And it is Bob's turn
  Then Bob sees a prominent "Your Turn" indicator
  And Alice sees "Waiting for Bob"
  And Carol sees "Waiting for Bob"
  And Bob's player card is highlighted
  And the other players' cards are dimmed
